Uganda’s Bunyoro Kingdom Wants 10% of Oil Revenue, Monitor Says

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-11-28T07:54:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-28/uganda-s-bunyoro-kingdom-wants-10-of-oil-revenue-monitor-says.html
Uganda ’s Bunyoro Kingdom, where oil
has been discovered, has asked the East African nation’s central
government to award it a 10 percent share of revenue from the
nation’s oil deposits, the  Daily Monitor  reported, citing
Yabeezi Kiiza, the kingdom’s prime minister.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala via Johannesburg at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
